### 2. Update Frequency / Timing

| Trigger | Frequency |
|---|---|
| **Commander boot** | Once at startup (initial seed write) |
| **Perreggcochran/dev/ child launch** | After every `launch_requested` → `launch_started` event (agent-driven, not timed) |
| **On failure/blocked** | Event-driven (on non-zero exit or prereq failure) |
| **Monitor reads** | **Every 5 seconds** (`sleep 5` at `stampede-monitor.sh:400`); during completion: `sleep 2` at line 328 |
| **Orphan/heartbeat check** | Every 5-second monitor loop; stale threshold = **180 seconds** (`ORPHAN_RECOVERY_AFTER=180`) |

There is **no periodic tick writing** — all writes are event-driven by the commander agent. The monitor only reads.

