#### 🟠 Race Condition: `reviews.jsonl` / `broadcasts.jsonl` Read During Concurrent Write
Commanders are told to "review other commanders' proposals in real time." If Commander A reads `proposals.jsonl` while Commander B is mid-append (before the newline is flushed), A may read a **partial/truncated JSON object**. The protocol says "Readers must tolerate absent files and malformed trailing lines" — but each commander agent (an LLM) may not actually implement that resilience.

#### 🟡 Inconsistency: `collab` dict stores `counts` but Nothing Updates Them
The `collab` dict (line 706) includes `'counts': {name: 0 for name in ledger_events}`. These counters are never incremented by any code — they are written once and never updated. The monitor or synthesizer has no way to observe proposal counts via this dict.

#### 🟡 Missing: No `adopt` Ledger File
The workflow sequence is `["propose","peer_review","improve","consensus","broadcast","adopt"]` but only five ledgers are created — `proposals`, `reviews`, `improvements`, `consensus`, `broadcasts`. There is **no `adopted.jsonl`** file created. "Adopt" is defined as placing `item_id`s into `bundle.json`, but there is no dedicated ledger to audit which items were adopted across commanders.

